<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="id7a74a665-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><ref href="/us/usc/t15/s278g–3">Section 278g–3 of this title</ref>, referred to in par. (2), was amended by <ref href="/us/pl/107/347/tIII/s303">Pub. L. 107–347, title III, § 303</ref>, <date date="2002-12-17">Dec. 17, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/2957">116 Stat. 2957</ref>, and, as so amended, did not contain a subsec. (f). A later amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/113/274/tII/s204/1">Pub. L. 113–274, title II, § 204(1)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-18">Dec. 18, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2980">128 Stat. 2980</ref>, redesignated subsec. (e) of <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s278g–3">section 278g–3 of this title</ref>, relating to definitions, as (f).</p>
</note>
